---
description: Architecture, schema, API, and data-model rules
globs:
  - "app/**/*.ts"
  - "app/**/*.tsx"
  - "lib/**/*.ts"
  - "prisma/**/*.prisma"
  - "components/**/*.ts"
  - "components/**/*.tsx"
---

Respect existing architecture:
- Next.js app router
- Prisma for schema and database access
- Supabase for storage
- modular product structure

Data modeling rules:
- favor explicit relationships over overloaded fields
- preserve separation between showings, open houses, visitors, follow-ups, transactions, commissions
- when representing different roles, model them clearly (listing agent, host agent, assistant, etc.)
- avoid introducing ambiguous route names or mixed terminology

API rules:
- route names and page titles must match product concepts
- do not label open houses as showings or vice versa
- preserve public/host/internal surface separation

Environment rules:
- use NEXT_PUBLIC_* only for browser-safe values
- server-only secrets must stay server-side
- do not move secrets into client code

Migration rules:
- if schema changes are introduced, explain migration impact
- do not silently break existing data flows
